<div class="source-grid" id="source-grid">

<!-- GENERAL SOURCES -->
<div class="source-card" data-tags="general equality">
<div class="source-icon">📊</div>
<div>
<div class="source-tags">
<span class="source-tag general">General</span>
<span class="source-tag equality">Equality</span>
</div>
<div class="source-name"><a href="https://hdr.undp.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Human Development Reports — Data Center</a></div>
<div class="source-org">United Nations Development Programme (UNDP)</div>
<div class="source-desc">The official HDI data centre. Compare countries by health, education, and standard of living. Also includes the Inequality-adjusted HDI (IHDI), Gender Development Index, and Multidimensional Poverty Index. Essential for any paper on development or equality.</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="source-card" data-tags="general equality freedom">
<div class="source-icon">🌍</div>
<div>
<div class="source-tags">
<span class="source-tag general">General</span>
<span class="source-tag equality">Equality</span>
<span class="source-tag freedom">Freedoms</span>
</div>
<div class="source-name"><a href="https://ourworldindata.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Our World in Data</a></div>
<div class="source-org">University of Oxford</div>
<div class="source-desc">Interactive charts and data on virtually every development topic: life expectancy, education, poverty, democracy, human rights, and more. Great for finding specific data points and visualising trends over time. Excellent for comparing countries.</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="source-card" data-tags="general equality">
<div class="source-icon">💰</div>
<div>
<div class="source-tags">
<span class="source-tag general">General</span>
<span class="source-tag equality">Equality</span>
</div>
