<div class="source-org">Wellbeing Research Centre, University of Oxford / Gallup / UN SDSN</div>
<div class="source-desc">Ranks countries by self-reported happiness using six factors: income, social support, life expectancy, freedom to make choices, generosity, and corruption perceptions. Useful for any priority — it shows what actually makes people feel their lives are going well. Finland has topped the rankings for nine consecutive years.</div>
