<!-- ========== TAB 4: CITATIONS ========== -->

<div class="panel" id="panel-citations">
<div class="card">
<h2>How to Cite Your Sources</h2>
<p style="margin-bottom:1rem;">You need <strong>two types</strong> of citation in your paper: in-text citations (inside your writing) and a reference list (at the end).</p>

```
<h3 style="margin-top:1rem;">In-Text Citations</h3>
<p style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Every time you use a fact, number, or idea from a source, put a short citation in brackets immediately after it.</p>
<div class="citation-example">
Finland ranks first in the World Happiness Report for the ninth consecutive year <strong>(Gallup, 2026)</strong>.
</div>
<div class="citation-example">
Countries scoring above 50 on the Corruption Perceptions Index tend to be full democracies <strong>(Transparency International, 2025)</strong>.
</div>
<div class="citation-example">
Estonia leads the 2024 Environmental Performance Index with a score of 75.3, largely due to a 40% reduction in greenhouse gas emissions <strong>(Yale Center for Environmental Law & Policy, 2024)</strong>.
</div>

<div class="tip-box">
<div class="tip-title">Format</div>
<p style="font-size:0.9rem;"><strong>(Organisation or Author, Year)</strong> — that's all you need in the text. The full URL goes in your reference list.</p>
</div>

<h3 style="margin-top:1.5rem;">Reference List</h3>
<p style="margin-bottom:0.5rem;">At the end of your paper, list every source you cited. Use this format:</p>
<div class="citation-example">
Organisation Name. (Year). <em>Title of Report or Page</em>. URL
</div>
<p style="margin-top:0.5rem; font-size:0.9rem;">For example:</p>
<div class="citation-example">
UNDP. (2025). <em>Human Development Report 2025</em>. https://hdr.undp.org/
</div>
<div class="citation-example">
Freedom House. (2026). <em>Freedom in the World 2026: The Growing Shadow of Autocracy</em>. https://freedomhouse.org/report/freedom-world
</div>
<div class="citation-example">
Transparency International. (2025). <em>Corruption Perceptions Index 2024</em>. https://www.transparency.org/en/cpi/2024
</div>

<div class="warning-box">
<div class="warning-title">The #1 citation mistake from last assessment</div>
<p style="font-size:0.9rem;">Many of you had strong research but <strong>zero in-text citations</strong> in your final writing. The research was there; the credit wasn't. This time, every claim that comes from a source needs a bracket.</p>
</div>
</div>
```

